body: "# Generate completions, MCP tool registrations, and command docs from the contracts table\n\nMake `src/sdk/cli-contracts.ts` the single machine-consumed source of truth for every derived command surface: bash/zsh/fish completions, the MCP tool registration table, and the command reference docs. Today each of these is hand-maintained, which is why adding one command requires touching ~10 sites (commands/index.ts, register-mutation.ts, mcp/server.ts, cli-contracts names/actions/flag-contracts/schema-contracts/params, commands/contracts.ts, three completion scripts, docs, vitest.config.ts) and why contract drift keeps recurring (pm-zx13, pm-4os2, GH-449/pm-kjbh are all instances of the same class).\n\n## Why now\nGrammar principle 6 of this epic's charter says \"help tiers, completions, MCP tools, and docs are all generated from the same contract table\", but only the help tier has an implementing child (pm-e2bq). Doing this BEFORE the noun-verb consolidation lands means every consolidation child (pm-pfqi, pm-tqel, pm-tnud, …) updates one table instead of ten files, and the alias shim layer (pm-0z7n) gets its alias list from the same table.\n\n## Scope\n- Completions: generate bash/zsh/fish from the contract table at build time (checked-in generated output + a drift gate, matching the contracts:update pattern).\n- MCP: derive tool registration (names, action mapping, input schemas) from PM_TOOL_ACTIONS + SCHEMA_CONTRACTS so a missing SCHEMA_CONTRACTS entry is a build-time error, not a `contracts --full` crash (PR#357 trap).\n- Docs: generate the per-command reference skeleton (flags, defaults, aliases) into docs, keeping prose sections hand-written.\n- Reduce the documented new-command wiring checklist to: implement handler + add one contracts entry + prose docs.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\nA drift gate fails CI when completions/MCP table/docs skeleton do not match the contract table; the new-command wiring checklist in docs shrinks to ≤3 manual sites; existing surfaces are byte-stable or intentionally improved (snapshot-reviewed).\n\n## Out of scope\nThe help-tier renderer (pm-e2bq), the grammar/alias decisions themselves (ADR pm-pbyu), SDK promotion of contracts (covered by pm-usfg children)."
